🎢 Adventure
These act as preferences rather than strict requirements.

4. Generating Results
Using the questionnaire responses, location (if available), and weather (if available), UpNext generates 5–10 highly personalized recommendations.

Recommendation Logic
Recommendations should be ranked according to how well they match the user's complete situation.
The app should consider:
Desired mood
Energy level
Group size
Companions
Indoor/outdoor preference
Time available
Budget
Transportation
Maximum travel distance
Current time
Selected interests
Current weather (if available)
Current location (if available)
Every recommendation should receive a relevance score and be displayed from most relevant to least relevant.

Recommendation Quality Rules
The recommendation engine should always:
Recommend the activities that best match the user's responses.
Prioritize quality over quantity.
Recommend activities that can realistically be done immediately.
Avoid duplicate or nearly identical recommendations.
Maximize variety while remaining highly relevant.
Prefer nearby places that are currently open.
Ensure activities fit within the available time.
Stay within the user's budget.
Never recommend activities that clearly conflict with the user's responses.
Continue providing excellent recommendations even if permissions are denied.

Types of Recommendations
When Location Is Available
Provide a balanced mix of:
At-Home Activities
Examples:
Cooking
Crocheting
Painting
Photography
Home workouts
Reading
Learning a language
Coding
Meditation
Board games
DIY projects
Each should include:
Tutorial videos
Helpful articles
Reference photos
Guides
so the user can begin immediately.

Nearby Places
Examples:
Museums
Restaurants
Parks
Arcades
Escape rooms
Cafés
Hiking trails
Shopping centers
Sports venues
Bowling
Mini golf
Events
Recommendations should use real nearby locations.

When Location Is Not Available
Do not recommend nearby places.
Only recommend personalized activities that can be done without knowing the user's location.

Every Recommendation Includes
Title
Short description
Why it matches the user's responses
Community rating
Save for Later
Schedule option
Supporting links
For DIY activities:
Tutorial videos
Guides
Reference photos
For places:
Address
Opening hours
Photos
Reviews

Get Me There
Every place recommendation includes a Get Me There button.
Selecting it opens an Uber ride request using Uber's API or deep link so the user can immediately travel to the destination.
If Uber is unavailable or not installed, provide an appropriate fallback.

5. Dynamic Background
Before completing the questionnaire:
Black background
Soft blue and purple accent lighting
After recommendations are generated, the background changes to reflect the overall mood.
Examples:
Adventure → Deep Red / Orange
Relaxing → Soft Blue
Creative → Purple
Social → Warm Yellow
Additional mood-color mappings can be added later.
The transition should feel smooth and premium.

6. Recommendation Feedback
After completing an activity, users can rate it.
👍 Loved It
😐 It Was Okay
👎 Not For Me
This feedback should gradually improve future recommendations while still prioritizing the user's current questionnaire responses. There should be 10 end results 

7. Empty State Handling
The app should never simply display "No Results Found."
If suitable recommendations are limited because of:
Late hours
Bad weather
Limited budget
Short available time
Permission restrictions
the app should still generate the best possible alternatives.

8. Success Criteria
UpNext should always:
Help users stop scrolling and start doing something enjoyable.
Recommend activities that genuinely fit the user's current situation.
Prioritize relevance over quantity.
Balance variety with personalization.
Make recommendations users can act on immediately.
Continue functioning even when permissions are denied.
Deliver a fast, simple, enjoyable experience from start to finish.

Open Items for Future Development
Final color palette for mood categories.
API source(s) for nearby places and activities.
Questionnaire flow (fully sequential vs. optional skipping).
Uber API integration details.
Calendar integration for scheduled activities.
User accounts and saved preferences.
Machine learning or personalization improvements based on user feedback.
Additional recommendation sources (local events, seasonal activities, etc.).
Should learn from mistakes 

I want you to improve the recommendation system and the Quick Search feature. Please follow these instructions exactly.
1. Remove repetitive recommendations
Many of the recommendations are currently too similar. Do not suggest the same type of activity multiple times with slightly different wording. Every recommendation should be unique and provide genuine variety while still matching the user's questionnaire responses. Focus on quality rather than quantity.
2. Make recommendations actually match the user's answers
The recommendation engine needs to use all of the questionnaire responses together when deciding what to recommend.
For example, I selected:
100% energy
10 people
High activity
The app recommended making pasta at home, which does not match my responses at all.
Someone with very high energy and a large group should receive recommendations such as:
Escape rooms
Bowling
Go-karting
Mini golf
Paintball
Trampoline parks
Sports activities
Arcades
Group hikes
Events
Restaurants suitable for groups
Other fun group activities nearby
Recommendations should always make logical sense based on the user's mood, energy level, group size, interests, available time, budget, transportation, indoor/outdoor preference, weather (if available), and location (if available). The app should never ignore these answers when generating recommendations.
3. Use real places, not generic suggestions
For every place-based recommendation, use Google Maps Places API (or another supported Places API) to find real nearby locations.
Do not display recommendations such as:
"Go to a coffee shop."
"Visit a park."
"Go to a restaurant."
Instead, display actual nearby businesses.
Each place should include:
Business name
Address
Distance
Opening hours
Rating
Photos
Short description
"Get Me There" button
This should apply to coffee shops, restaurants, museums, parks, cinemas, arcades, shopping centres, hiking trails, gyms, libraries, and every other place-based recommendation.
4. Fix the Quick Search
The Quick Search is not working correctly.
For example, when I searched "coffee shop," the app did not return any nearby coffee shops.
The search should work like this:
If the user searches for a place, return real nearby businesses using Google Maps Places API (or another supported Places API).
If the user searches for an activity, return relevant activities and nearby places where that activity can be done.
The search results should always match exactly what the user typed.
5. Use live data whenever possible
If location permission has been granted, always use live location data to recommend places that actually exist and are currently open whenever possible.
Do not invent businesses, use placeholder data, or return generic suggestions when real nearby places are available.
6. Overall goal
The app should feel like a genuine personal activity finder, not a random activity generator. Every recommendation should be personalized, realistic, actionable, and based on the user's current situation. If the user gives answers that indicate they want something energetic, social, relaxing, creative, or adventurous, the recommendations should clearly reflect those choices. Every place recommendation should correspond to a real location that the user can visit immediately. and make the color more related to the suggestions 
I'd like to redesign the beginning of the app to create a more informative and user-friendly experience before the questionnaire starts.
Instead of taking users directly into the survey, add a starting/home page that acts as the main hub of the app. This page should include:
A Saved & Scheduled Activities Calendar, where users can easily view activities they've saved for later or scheduled for specific dates and times. Users should be able to open the calendar, view upcoming plans, edit or remove scheduled activities, and mark activities as completed once they've done them.
A section displaying the user's recently completed or previously selected activities, allowing them to revisit ideas they enjoyed or repeat activities they liked.
A brief introduction explaining what UpNext is, how it works, and what makes it different from other recommendation apps. This should emphasize that UpNext doesn't provide random suggestions—instead, it personalizes recommendations based on the user's current mood, energy level, available time, budget, interests, weather, location (if permitted), and other responses to help them find the best possible activity for that specific moment.
A clear "Start Questionnaire" button that begins the personalized recommendation process.
I'd also like to add a Quick Search option to this home page. This should consist of a small search bar where users can type something simple, such as "coffee shops," "things to do indoors," "movie ideas," or "creative hobbies." Instead of going through the full questionnaire, the app should provide quicker, simpler recommendations based only on the search query. This gives users the choice between receiving highly personalized recommendations through the questionnaire or finding something quickly with a simple search.
Finally, I'd still like the questionnaire itself to be improved by grouping related questions together so that each screen contains approximately 2–4 related questions, rather than only one question per page. This will reduce the number of times users need to press Continue, making the experience feel faster and more natural while keeping the interface clean and easy to navigate.
